[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering metadata in tests**\n\nI'm pondering whether the untracked metadata is something that was preexisting or if it belongs to some kind of support feature. My focus is on testing changes, so I really shouldn’t include the metadata unless it’s essential. Still, I want to inspect it because it might relate to past workflows. It seems like tests need certain metadata for reachability in native images. But, I also need to decide if my changes are isolated enough to commit without that metadata involved.\n\n**Exploring Native Image functionality**\n\nI’m trying to understand how Native Image handles class loading and if its metadata can define classes. I wonder how evaluateString passed if that’s the case. Maybe the test results are based on a previous build before I made changes. Existing tests might run on JVM while the native image compiles them but doesn’t execute them. Gradle does seem to have a process for compiling and testing native code. I’m also curious if dynamic class definitions are supported for generated classes in this context.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0dd64e254dc1c5ec0169f10f8e9100819197379c83e68b3fe7\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8Q-WH2etr1FCgMhwqz0Mm6kIZMg9IugHZmw1X0Ugk2t2tPibUPE8hDPNPrHKCp1VYlCAl7ecyF8FQlTW82U6C_sw0wBTnx-OQmfjRTfOc9UcPsgPKGnrKdl2unRgn2470oUNqZP-swwa9TtmZs1B5ccEpx_HYbRnqTaumRi2tydMjjd6L1mm5BdQyAuK32nBLnDSKpTwj8R-NbfM1cJxY6sqTAYhtiEMCnPm2YGJrxe3TYdSn-9eRF6W4Ns4bq2h_m48eXMfEA0YAIeOtT8OaGQpkbPEgPJhyLxdpqJvPdHo1CV3gW-aQYgwpGX2yjiv3lrSAiUvy2yMFRbtT6mmxDANvAL1E7RwcPNPTICSHML_ycws1DMEliKXEuyt9LseaHUZia8WplzwXgJ1bOAFb0BeJqeJ7K3Ahdv3fdAMYDmFcqzp3-1NNOWHaCJLr4Bjk6HzvMtLuSAHaCNCpfdEhkZMYCHNXMGW_OXOf8QHNYl_nDTuMetWkq3CSxHhlCf_RzoPaSGsumoZLx3TfRR_Y6T_lw8GhkwKY_hrbQEE-mEay4MAcvdPOIYBHdc-SIthF0UX4OuG7-IziHAmrgj7pUCybiZRhwwkZo9p2KSC5wQp4B1ojJsSRvxF4Y8tVcGXRJHlsm3HGSL8jyM3lFwC1cAZTSuGdYMy1DiyTE-1